covidLtcNotes.notes:
South Carolina reports long-term care data for Nursing Homes and Community Residential Care Facilities (CRCF). Based on South Carolina’s definition of a CRCF, it is categorized as an Assisted Living Facility in the data set. CTP does not include cases and deaths for the following facility types: "Intermediate Care Facility for Individuals with Intellectual Disabilities" and "Residential Treatment Facility for Children & Adolescents.". The state reports cumulative and outbreak cases and deaths by type of facility. Data is reported twice a week on Tuesday and Friday. South Carolina’s data is cumulative since April 3. South Carolina reports facility-level data.

June 25, 2020: CTP carried over the outbreak data from June 22. 

August 3, 2020: Cumulative nursing home staff deaths decreased from nine to two in South Carolina’s reporting.

September 3, 2020: SC did not report their 30-day active list, so CTP was unable to record outbreak totals. 

September 10, 2020: South Carolina resumed reporting their 30-day active list.
